SIMPLE: truant
RECORDS: 4

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Truant
<hw>Tru"ant</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>truand</ets>, OF.
<ets>truant</ets>, a vagrant, beggar; of Celtic origin; cf. W.
<ets>tru</ets>, <ets>truan</ets>, wretched, miserable, <ets>truan</ets>
a wretch, Ir. <ets>trogha</ets> miserable, Gael. <ets>truaghan</ets> a
poor, distressed, or wretched creature, <ets>truagh</ets>
wretched.]</ety> <def>One who stays away from business or any duty;
especially, one who stays out of school without leave; an idler; a
loiterer; a shirk.</def> <rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I have a <qex>truant</qex> been to chivalry.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>To play truant</b></col>, <cd>to stray away; to loiter;
especially, to stay out of school without leave.</cd> <rj><au>Sir T.
Browne</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Truant</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Truant
<hw>Tru"ant</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Wandering from business or duty;
loitering; idle, and shirking duty; <as>as, a <ex>truant</ex>
boy</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>While <qex>truant</qex> Jove, in infant pride,⟦br⟧
Played barefoot on Olympus' side.</q> <rj><qau>Trumbull.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Truant</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Truant
<hw>Tru"ant</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>truander</ets>.]</ety> <def>To idle away time; to loiter, or
wander; to play the truant.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>By this means they lost their time and <qex>truanted</qex> on the
fundamental grounds of saving knowledge.</q>
<rj><qau>Lowell.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Truant</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Truant
<hw>Tru"ant</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To idle away; to waste.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I dare not be the author⟦br⟧
Of <qex>truanting</qex> the time.</q> <rj><qau>Ford.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Truantly</ent>⟦br⟧
